com.ojcoleman.europa.core

Class Individual<G extends Genotype<?>,F extends Function<?,?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ojcoleman.europa.configurable.Observable
      • com.ojcoleman.europa.configurable.ConfigurableBase
        • com.ojcoleman.europa.configurable.PrototypeBase
          • com.ojcoleman.europa.core.Individual<G,F>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Stringable, java.lang.Comparable<Individual<?,?>>

    public class Individual<G extends Genotype<?>,F extends Function<?,?>>
extends PrototypeBase
implements java.lang.Comparable<Individual<?,?>>
    Represents an individual in the Population used in the evolutionary algorithm. An individual is a container for a Genotype, The Function to be evaluated (transcribed from the Genotype if the Genotype is not also the Function), and the resulting EvaluationData.
    Author:
    O. J. Coleman
